				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Stealing Guard's Kills with Charm<a name="16484"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 21 04 1:54 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It IS considered an exploit because NPC guards are basically part of the environment and you are using their AI to do your job for you so that you get full XP when you and your abilities only did a fraction of the damage.  When you swarm kite, your abilities are directly responsible for 100% of the damage to your targets, since you have to have the ability to charm and maintain it.  Having a guard do 90% of the damage, then finishing off the mob is very definitely an exploit.  If you keep this up, expect a visit from a GM someday and a warning.</span></td>
