				<td colspan="2"><span>Hum, 
<br />
I have a related question, but I put it in a separated post to make the two subjects distinct.
<br />

<br />
When I was in Karana, experimentating with AOE songs, it happenned that I would be over doing my agro, then run to the guards with a swarm of mobs, run around the guard while he kills most of the swarm, <b>and get killed leaving a single damaged mob that I could kill by myself.</b>
<br />

<br />
It would take some work to repeat it regularly, and the overcost (too many mobs and guards killed for the XP of a single mob) would be ridiculous, but it would be doable. I guess it would also be considered an exploit?
<br />

<br />
It is amusing to think that in order to avoid this kind of actions, the guards could become more intelligent, and decide to get bored at a char who is always coming to them for help, and lower his faction when they get killed because of him. No ?  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
(I hope I don't get the reputation of an exploit seeker, 
<br />
I just like to think about the system. Don't like doing 100 times the same things anyway, wouldn't have repeated guard kills stealing more than, say, 10 times before getting bored of it.) <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" />
